  "_doc": "Reference table for DORA economic_impact_eur calibration. Each entry maps an estimated sim shock_units value to the real public cost in EUR millions of a known historical incident. Used by core.dora.economic_impact._calibrated_alpha() to fit the OLS slope \u03b1 (EUR per shock unit). Update via scripts/calibrate_dora_alpha.py and refit nightly via the GitHub Actions cron. Sources cited per row \u2014 when public, the regulatory disclosure / parliamentary inquiry / earnings call is preferred over press summaries.",
